quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  25,56,We have only sent you to give glad tidings and as a Warner
  25,57,"Say, \"I ask you for no reward for this, save that whoever will may choose a way unto his Lord"
  25,58,And rely you upon the Living One who dies not; and celebrate His praise; He is sufficient as Knower about the faults of His servants
  25,59,"He who created the heavens and the earth, and what is between them, in six days, and then mounted the Throne; the Beneficent! Ask any one who is aware concerning Him"
  25,60,"And when it is said unto them, \"Adore you the Beneficent\", they say, \"What is the Beneficent? Shall we adore what you do order us?\" And it only increases their aversion"
  25,61,"Blessed be He who placed in the heavens mansions (constellations) of stars, and has placed therein a great lamp and an illuminating moon"
  25,62,"And He it is who made the night and the day alternating, for him who desires to remember or who desires thankfulness"
  25,63,"And the faithful servants of the Beneficent are those who walk upon the earth modestly, and when the ignorant (or foolish) address them, answer, \"Peace"
  25,64,"And those who pass the night before their Lord, prostrate and standing"
  25,65,"And those who say, \"Our Lord! Avert from us the doom of hell; verily, its wrath is indeed a grievous affliction"
  25,66,"Verily, indeed an evil abode and state"
  25,67,"And those who when they spend are neither extravagant nor miserly, but who always take their stand between the two"